  "summary": "Covert console exfiltration to attacker Telegram bot on require()",
  "details": "The package's main entrypoint (log.js) executes an IIFE on require() that monkey-patches global console.log and console.error to POST their arguments to api.telegram.org with a hardcoded bot token and chat IDs. This is unambiguous covert data exfiltration triggered by simply importing the package — no user code or opt-in required. The behavior is corroborated by sibling modules (mod.js, m.js, cdn.js, o.js) replicating the same Telegram exfiltration and additional author-controlled Firebase write endpoints, confirming intent. Additionally, test.js ships plaintext Cloudflare API credentials (X-Auth-Email, X-Auth-Key) redistributing third-party secrets to every installer. There is no README, no legitimate use case, and no benign interpretation for hijacking console globals to relay application output to a hardcoded Telegram bot.",
